lib/src/charsmap_trie.dart ports the trie-traversal *structure* (not the
literal source) of the following third-party project:

  spm_precompiled
  https://github.com/huggingface/spm_precompiled
  Copyright (c) Hugging Face
  Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0

Specifically, `CharsmapTrie._commonPrefixSearch` and `CharsmapTrie.transform`
port the algorithm shape of `spm_precompiled`'s `DoubleArray::common_prefix_search`
and `Precompiled::transform`, and `CharsmapTrie.normalize` ports the
grapheme-cluster-first, fall-back-to-single-char strategy of
`Precompiled::normalize_string`. This was necessary because no existing Dart
implementation of SentencePiece's `precompiled_charsmap` Darts double-array
trie format could be found — see `plan_0_06_wi11_xlmr_tokenizer.md` (in the
`kmdb` repository) and this package's `README.md` for the full investigation
and rationale.

